<inglise> Understanding in Respect of Waivers of Obligations under the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade 1994 </inglise>
<eesti> vl12 RT II 1999, 22, 123 GATT 1994 ALUSEL V&Otilde;ETUD KOHUSTUSTE PEATAMISE K&Auml;SITUSLEPE </eesti>
<inglise> Members hereby agree as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga lepivad liikmed kokku j&auml;rgmises: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A request for a waiver or for an extension of an existing waiver shall describe the measures which the Member proposes to take, the specific policy objectives which the Member seeks to pursue and the reasons which prevent the Member from achieving its policy objectives by measures consistent with its obligations under GATT 1994. </inglise>
<eesti> Peatamistaotluses v&otilde;i kehtiva peatamise pikendamise taotluses tuleb kirjeldada meetmeid, mida asjaomane liige pakub, konkreetseid eesm&auml;rke, mille poole see liige p&uuml;&uuml;dleb, ja p&otilde;hjusi, miks liikmel ei ole v&otilde;imalik saavutada oma eesm&auml;rke meetmete abil, mis on koosk&otilde;las tema kohustustega GATT 1994 j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Any waiver in effect on the date of entry into force of the WTO Agreement shall terminate, unless extended in accordance with the procedures above and those of Article IX of the WTO Agreement, on the date of its expiry or two years from the date of entry into force of the WTO Agreement, whichever is earlier. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui WTO lepingu j&otilde;ustumise kuup&auml;eval kehtivat mis tahes peatamist ei ole pikendatud koosk&otilde;las eespool ja WTO lepingu IX artiklis s&auml;testatud protseduuridega, l&otilde;petatakse k&otilde;nealune peatamine selle kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemise kuup&auml;eval v&otilde;i kahe aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dudes WTO lepingu j&otilde;ustumise kuup&auml;evast vastavalt sellele, kumb nimetatud kuup&auml;evadest on varasem. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Any Member considering that a benefit accruing to it under GATT 1994 is being nullified or impaired as a result of: </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liige, kes leiab, et tema GATT 1994 alusel saadavat kasu muudetakse olematuks v&otilde;i v&auml;hendatakse, sest: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the failure of the Member to whom a waiver was granted to observe the terms or conditions of the waiver, or </inglise>
<eesti> a) liige, kellele anti peatamisluba, ei ole v&otilde;imeline j&auml;rgima k&otilde;nealuse peatamise tingimusi, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the application of a measure consistent with the terms and conditions of the waiver may invoke the provisions of Article XXIII of GATT 1994 as elaborated and applied by the Dispute Settlement Understanding. </inglise>
<eesti> b) rakendati peatamise tingimustega koosk&otilde;las olevat meedet, v&otilde;ib tugineda GATT 1994 XXIII artikli s&auml;tetele, mis on t&auml;psustatud ja rakendatud vaidluste lahendamise k&auml;situsleppes. </eesti>
 